        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_arawyn_1" n="1" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>arawyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>aryd</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>arawun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>arud</orth></form></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>опалять на огне</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>scorch on fire</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>lægæn jæ rīxītæ acarydysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у мужчины обгорели усы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the man's mustache got burned</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Wyryzmæg ærdægaryddytæj jæxī wæxstæj raftydta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Урузмаг полуобгоревший снялся с вертела</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Uruzmag, half-burnt, took himself off the spit</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Нарт._сказ."
                            /><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>qybyly artyl acaraw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>опали поросенка на огне</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>scorch the pig on the fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Burimæ wyd... xærz aryd fysy qus</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у Бури было хорошо опаленное на огне баранье ухо</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Buri had a ram's ear, well seared by the fire</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_F."/><biblScope>1957 III
                            28</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æz dær arud ditæj... mæxe uxstæj tuxæj raftudton</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>я тоже, обгоревший,с трудом снял себя с вертела</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I, too, burned, with difficulty removed myself from the spit</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            14</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Допуская исходное значение ‘коптить’, ‘чернить, держа над
                    огнем’, мы видим в %iarawyn%i старое сращение преверба %iа-%i с основой
                    %i*raw-%i ‘марать’, ‘пачкать’, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ā-lūdan</w>
                        <gloss><q>марать</q></gloss></mentioned> (из %iā-lāv-%i: <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."
                        /><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>); сюда же, может быть, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>alwōyəl, a(w)law-</w>
                        <gloss><q>опалять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>обжигать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>жарить</q></gloss></mentioned>; <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āludan</w></mentioned> связывают с <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>lutum</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>λύμα</w>
                        <gloss><q>грязь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>polluo</w>
                        <gloss><q>пачкать</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. В ос. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wyrawyn"/> ‘жечь’ имеем ту же основу %iraw%i, сращенную с
                    превербом %iwy-%i. В медиальном значении тот же глагол с закономерным
                    ослаблением гласного основы (%iau%i → %iu%i) находим в д. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_arujun"/> ‘опаляться огнем’. %bБалк.%b <mentioned
                        xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>araun, arawan</w>
                        <gloss><q>сковорода для поджаривания хлеба</q></gloss></mentioned>
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ЯМ"/><biblScope>I
                        77</biblScope></bibl>) отражает <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>arawæn</w></mentioned>. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arujun"
                    />.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Assuming the original meaning ‘smoke’, ‘blacken holding over
                    fire’, we see in %iarawyn%i the old contraction of the preverb %iа-%i and the
                    stem %i*raw-%i ‘soil’, ‘make dirty’, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>ā-lūdan</w>
                        <gloss><q>soil</q></gloss></mentioned> (from %iā-lāv-%i: <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."
                        /><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl>); maybe the following words are related to
                    it as well: <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/>
                        <w>alwōyəl, a(w)law-</w>
                        <gloss><q>scorch</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>burn</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fry</q></gloss></mentioned>; some people relate <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āludan</w></mentioned> to <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>lutum</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>λύμα</w>
                        <gloss><q>mud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>polluo</w>
                        <gloss><q>make dirty</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. In Ossetic <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_wyrawyn"/> ‘burn’ there is the same stem %iraw%i, contracted
                    with the preverb %iwy-%i. In the middle voice the same verb with the regular
                    stem vowel weakening (%iau%i → %iu%i) is found in Digor <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_arujun"/> ‘be scorched with fire’. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>araun, arawan</w>
                        <gloss><q>frying pan for toasting bread</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ЯМ"/><biblScope>I 77</biblScope></bibl>)
                    reflects <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/>
                        <w>arawæn</w></mentioned>. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arujun"
                    />.</etym>
            </entry>
